The Treatment Advocacy Center (TAC) is a controversial national U.S. nonprofit organization dedicated to passing and implementing laws that permit the use of legal force and coercion in order to treat people diagnosed with severe mental illnesses such as schizophrenia and bipolar disorder. Towards this end, the organization promotes laws, policies and practices and the development of new treatment methods. Among the organizationâ€™s principal activities are promoting the passage and implementation of involuntary outpatient treatment (IOT) laws, also referred to as assisted outpatient treatment laws (AOT),
